<b translate="no" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> 490052: Printhead temperature result too high during Waveform calibration</b> </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-F1F93D5E-1723-411F-B671-83D207392D5F"><p class="- topic/p ">During waveform calibration the needed the temperature of the printheads is too low. The needed temperature is related to the viscosity of the ink.
</p></abstract><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-40130844-4AAD-45CF-B100-382D6CFE9C6D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Collect</b> </title><p class="- topic/p "> 
<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Patterns in calibration print</u> 
</p><table id="GUID-970ACB1A-D670-40CA-A2E1-C2075EBCEA07" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="7.27*" class="- topic/colspec "/><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> C1640/C1650
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-1BF8F819-6D5B-49BC-AAE4-F8B4205EC2AC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-67890912-0513-41AC-BD86-2B3571D20F32-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-67890912-0513-41AC-BD86-2B3571D20F32-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> C1630/CMxx
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-DDF75818-E267-4EA2-B181-83D1F3E960E1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A913CCAA-D245-4F9E-AD95-E2A3D38AC9C3-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A913CCAA-D245-4F9E-AD95-E2A3D38AC9C3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "> 
<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Calibration step</u> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This warning is generated during the calibration step "PrintheadWaveforms" which is part of one the following calibration sequences:
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- Printhead calibration via the UI
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- SDS 04-6-026: “Execute printhead calibrations [Special Tests]”
</p></section><section id="GUID-535E955C-AEAD-486C-9DE2-94BB174A9C89" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Analyse/Repair</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the expired ink from the system by following procedure "<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u "> 02 The (expired) ink replacement procedure including flushing tubes</u>" in the TSM. Afterwards redo the calibration.
</p></section><section id="GUID-8B7545A8-5BF5-43C7-A38F-5EBD4C1E85A3" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Prevent ink to expire in the engine.
</p></section><section id="GUID-B4E38C1A-E1B4-4DD7-AA29-44241BA7D81A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">During waveform calibration the temperature of the printheads is adjusted to set the correct viscosity of the ink. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This is needed to get a uniform dropletsize. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When this setpoint is out of range the viscosity of the ink itself is not what it supposed to be.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-F2864082-F34C-4657-B37E-EA7C5343FE90.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
